net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component

Class AbstractButton

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.AbstractButton
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<Component>, LocaleContextSource, CardContainerSelector, Component, ListCellRenderer, TableCellRenderer, TreeCellRenderer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MenuItem, PushButton, TextButton, ToggleButton

    public abstract class AbstractButton
extends ComponentImpl
implements TableCellRenderer, TreeCellRenderer, ListCellRenderer, CardContainerSelector, java.lang.Cloneable

    A component that is a base class for buttons. This class provides common fields such as labels and state. All buttons have a selection state, either selected or unselected. The subclass medium layer will decide how this state is reflected. A subclass is not required to provide different behavior based on selection state.

    This class provides no functionality when the button is clicked. Override the click() method to provide functionality.

    Implementations of this class may be cell renderers. The cell value will affect the button label unless other wise indicated by the implementation documentation. If the label is explicitly set it will be constant for all cells. If it is left as the default or set to null the label will take the cell value. The appropriate cell renderer method must be called for subclass of this class to behave correctly as cell renderers.

    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

        public Element getHTMLElement()
        Description copied from interface: Component
        Get the top level elements this component will output in its current state. This should not included the entire content model.

        For example, if your code outputs the following, <p><span><b></b></span></p>, then you should only return one element that is a "p"; NOT "p, span, b".

        All configuration elements should be nested within this top element, or other arrangements should be made with the inner keeper.

      • init

        public void init()
        Description copied from interface: Component

        Called when a Component is first attached to a WindowManager. This means the Component should have valid return values from getApplication(), getLocaleContext(), getParent(). It is preferable to have all construction of the Component go here since a valid LocaleContext, Application object, etc., are available.

        When overriding this method, be sure to call the super class init(). init() is called only once for each Component. The parent component will have been init()ed before init() is called.

        NOTE: Do not call this method from application code. It is meant to be called by the WindowManager only.

        Specified by:
        init in interface Component
        Overrides:
        init in class ComponentImpl

      • preRenderProcess

        public void preRenderProcess(Request request,
                    Response response,
                    RendererEditorState<?> rendererEditorState)
        Allow the component to process any form fields before rendering. This method must be called by subclasses. Method calls on components, creating or destroying components, or nearly everything else having to do with the component tree and related data models must be done by queuing an event using EventQueue.queue(EventQueueElement). Otherwise you may get unexpected results. Calls click() on the button and sets the selection path if the renderer state is not null.
        Specified by:
        preRenderProcess in interface Component
        Overrides:
        preRenderProcess in class ComponentImpl
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        response - the response.
        rendererEditorState - the renderer / editor state, will be null if not using as a renderer / editor.
